(4, 0, 2, 3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 1, 0, 'Willits Emergency Fuels Reduction - Shaded Fuel Break and Prescribed Burn Project', null, 2540, 'Brooktrails and Pine Mountain', 3, null, 2019, 2022, 'This project will be in a densely populated Wildland Urban Interface (WUI) area with narrow roads and difficult accessibility. Currently, the communities of Brooktrails and Pine Mountain are limited to one all-weather, maintained access road. The fire hazard reduction will be accomplished by removing understory vegetation including brush and small trees along both sides of roads and by creating shaded fuel breaks. The removed material will be chipped or piled and burned. This project will have approximately 15 miles of shaded fuel break for approximately 720 acres. This will open a crucial secondary access for a densely populated urban interface area. The primary goal of the project is to improve roadways for safe evacuation routes. A second goal is to createpotential control lines in the event of a major wildfire from the east and west sides of the Willits valley. Low intensity prescribed burns will be conducted to reduce fuels and fire loading, while also achieving ecological goals. This project will reduce the number and intensity of wildfires and increase public safety. Shaded fuel break - hand crews will use hand tools and chainsaws and where feasible, skid steers and excavators. Prescribed burning will be conducted in the chaparral and grassland fuel types.'), 
