(4, 0, 2, 3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 1, 0, 'Sheep Grazing', null, 2540, 'Sea Ranch, Sonoma Coast', 2, 2019, null, null, 'This is a Fuel Reduction Project. The Sea Ranch Fuels Management Program (FMP), Specific Goal 6, emphasizes natural containment of fire size, especially with limited local firefighting personnel and equipment. It calls for livestock grazing to reduce fuels and the chance of fire ignition and spread to homes and infrastructure. Sheep grazing has been indigenous to The Sea Ranch for more than a century. The Project allows for similar grazing to continue as a natural fire prevention activity without using mechanized hand tools and motorized equipment, thereby eliminating emissions from such machinery. Such grazing is costeffective fire prevention in a critical and challenging environment.'), 
