(4, 0, 2, 3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 1, 0, 'Vegetation Management along Primary and Secondary Roads', 'Licensed contractors, FireSafe Sonoma, property owners, PG&E, Sonoma County TPW and Department of Emergency Management', 2540, 'Mill Creek Watershed', 3, null, 2020, 2020, 'Reduce/remove hazardous vegetation along primary and secondary road stosupport ingress and egress of residents evacuating, emergency vehicles, and reduce wildfire intensity. 
●Mill Creek Road is a county maintained road and the only primary road that serves the Mill Creek Area. Secondary roads are mostly privately maintained and are Mill Creek Lane Wallace Creek Road, Puccioni Road, and Palmer Creek Road 
●Identify critical areas and prioritize. Includes: Trimming over hanging branches, chipping all cut and dead material, removing (cut, pull and/ or spray) understory shrubs and pruning and/or selective removal of trees or tree branches that; A) pose a risk of falling on powerlines (Ignition); B) trees that may fall on the road and block access (Access & Evac); and C) lower level fuels (dead and alive) that are fuel for fire (Fuel Reduction).
●Identify funding and potential resources to implement work
●Include execution plan and align with available chipper programs
●Sonoma County Transportation and Public Works (TPW) has responsibility to keep the roadway clear of vegetation within their right of way. This distance is usually 5-10 feet from the edge of Mill Creek Road and the TPW maintained portion of Wallace Creek Road. Beyond the right of way, the responsibility becomes the individual property owner. Environmenta lreview will be required outside of the TPW right of way if government funding will be used for this project.'), 
