(4, 0, 2, 3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 1, 0, 'Vegetation Trends and Cycles in the Fire-Prone Landscapes of Lake, Napa, and Sonoma Counties', null, 2540, null, 2, 2020, null, null, 'We will examine the relationship between fire and vegetation across a region which has suffered some of California''s most devastating recent wildfires. Integrating historical and recent data (1870-2019), we will develop a detailed understanding of fire/vegetation cycles across a diverse landscape with wide variations in fire history (return intervals <10 to >100 yrs). Results will inform site-specific actions to minimize catastrophic fire and emissions, maximize carbon sequestration, and build public support.'), 
